Definition.WordDefinition: out-of-town \out-of-town\ adj. happening in or being of another town or city; as, an out-of-town tryout. [WordNet 1.5]
out-of-town adj : happening in or being of another town or city; "an out-of-town tryout"; "an out-of-town school"
